##When poor kids start taking online classes

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

During the outbreak, more than 70,000 students crammed into the "classroom in the sky" , developed at the Qingbei Internet school and the Gulou Primary School in Fuzhou. In addition to children from coastal cities, there are 8,000 children from poor mountain areas such as Min County in Gansu Province and Yangjialing in Yan 'An, Shaanxi Province. Separated from the North and south, rich and poor children, in a fortuitous opportunity, sitting in the "same classroom. ".

Year: 2020

Location: Fuzhou, Min County, Yangjialing, etc. 

What happens when 70,000 pupils squeeze into a class? Across the 2,000 km stretch from the South East Coast to the north west, the Some Random Place Somewhere of yangjialing in Yan'an is still cold in winter, while the coastal Gulou District is warm in early spring.

During the outbreak began the primary and secondary school online classes, so that these days the children sit in a "classroom. ".

Such classes have been running for nearly two weeks in the Qingbei online school system. Beginning in early February, schools across the country to take care of epidemic prevention and teaching, have opened online classes. In Gulou District, the heart of Fuzhou, education authorities have selected 152 teachers to create "classroom in the sky" through the bytedance's Qingbei live broadcast system.

In addition to Gulou District's nearly 70,000 primary school students, there are also students from Gulou District's designated help schools, and 8,000 children from remote mountainous areas such as Gansu and Shaanxi.

An Internet cable has unexpectedly flattened the educational gap created by geography and economic conditions. However, only those who were in the room were aware of the real impact and change of online education during the outbreak.

The "classroom in the sky" , which is connected with developed areas, allowed Pei Meiling, a Chinese teacher at Dongzhao Primary School in Min County, Gansu Province, to complete a home visit. More than half of the children in Dongzhao primary school are left-behind children. Usually their parents are not at home, so it is difficult for teachers to grasp the specific family situation of their children. Parents who have not yet gone out are using their mobile phones for their children's online lessons.

The end of the first day of online class, Pei Meiling in the class group to check the parents sent "learning punch card" photos. She found the photos to be mostly dark, pixelated and of a few tens of kilobytes in size.

Kids who study online shrink into the crevices of their desks and chairs, which are cluttered with clutter. Some children have no desk and have to stay in bed to study.

Photo | students listen to a live broadcast at Dongzhao Primary School in Min County, Gansu Province

Of the 37 students, only one was facing a computer, Pei noted, and the rest were using cell phones because there were no large-screen devices at home.

Pei's primary school, Dongzhao Primary School in Minxian County of Gansu Province, is a designated help school in Gulou District, Fuzhou. After the Chinese New Year, Pei Meiling was relieved to hear that she was going to have an online class with a school in a developed area.

Unlike urban children, who spend most of their spare time in training classes, Min County is poor and parents do not pay much attention to their children's education. Pei mei-ling has been worried that students in the countryside have "nothing to do" .

"classroom in the sky" online class, for children to open up a new learning channel, received notice, Pei Meiling immediately in the wechat group to inform parents of the news. The wechat group was set up five years ago. Most of the parents at Dongzhao primary school work in the city, and many of the students'parents and grandparents are in the group to ensure that the news is kept in place.

In order to play the efficiency of online class, Pei Meiling more assume the role of teaching assistant. Each time the notice broadcast class information, Pei mei-ling hair text after the notice, will read again with voice. Before this, a parent said "teacher I can not read, you say" , Pei Meiling has developed this habit.

When Pei Meiling with online class for home visits, Yang Jialing in Yan 'an Fuzhou Hope Primary School Teaching Feng Haiyan also anxious staring at the phone, help children and parents answer questions. Ms Fung had a visit to the second Central Primary School in drum tower, Fuzhou, and was deeply impressed by the differences between the two schools.

Whereas Drum Tower elementary school has a piano in every classroom, Yangjialing Fuzhou Hope Primary School only introduced electronic whiteboards a few years ago, and the hardware gap is huge.

Feng Haiyan remembers that when she first arrived at Hope Primary School, there was no multimedia equipment for public classes, so she had to write the key points on paper in advance and paste them on the blackboard when she gave lectures, which was equivalent to a PPT. Due to the shortage of teachers in the school, as an English teacher, she also taught music, art.

"Gulou District" by the sea is a long way away for students in Yangjialing. In 20 years of teaching, Feng Haiyan is still the first contact net class. With a sense of wonder, she opened the web site early on the day of the live lesson and waited. At 9 pm, the teacher from Gulou District appeared on the screen, and Feng looked to the upper left, where more than sixteen thousand people were watching.

In this invisible classroom, students from the Yan 'an area and students from the coastal city are linked together by a screen.

Feng Haiyan, a village teacher, was pleasantly surprised by the live-broadcast lecture. She thought it would be an opportunity for rural children to "broaden their horizons. ".

This Spring Festival, Xiao Mingjuan, a teacher at the Gulou experimental primary school in Fuzhou, did not return to her mother's home for the first time. She was nervous about her assignment as a live-streaming teacher for "classroom in the sky. ".

Gulou District has set up five schools specifically for live coverage, and they're well-equipped. The real challenge comes from the 8,000 children from the mountains, who are learning at different levels than Gulou District's children, and who are teaching in different materials, and the established teaching model certainly doesn't apply.

The second challenge for Xiao is how to make the course understandable to more than 10,000 students with different backgrounds. In the past, Xiao Mingjuan had to face groups of students in class. Now, she has to face three cameras. Without timely feedback, it is difficult to get used to it, and even more difficult to adapt to it, usually 40 minutes in class, now live classes on 20 minutes. Past experiences and teaching patterns don't work anymore.

"Some interaction needs to be added, to anticipate how the students will answer. " Imagining herself facing more than 10,000 students, Xiao Mingjuan's pressure is even greater.

Just like a TV program planner, Xiao Mingjuan writes the lesson plan first, then prepares the lesson in groups. After having the script, she then discusses the courseware with the teaching and research staff through the video to understand the skills of the card time and the sequential link. During Rehearsals, she practiced in front of a mirror to make sure there were no convoluted, redundant words, so that the lesson would be over in 20 minutes.

In order to ensure the quality of online courses, the "classroom in the air" project team of Qingbei net school has also trained the teachers. From February 2, Qingbei net school every day to arrange 4 online training for teachers and management personnel for a comprehensive system of Operation Training.

"unlike full-time anchors, some of the teachers are older, and it's difficult for them to add cameras and courseware, " said Liu Yun, the program's director. Some of the teachers are teaching live for the first time.

Taking into account the Western country children, Xiao Mingjuan's curriculum is not difficult, pictures and text, in order to let all students can hear, she deliberately slowed down the speed of speech.

In front of the camera, Xiao Mingjuan took off a mask that affected her pronunciation. She wore a fuchsia sweater to match the dark blue background of the courseware. Imagine the students in front of the camera listening to the class, Xiao Mingjuan raised her right hand, began to teach.

According to Xiao Mingjuan, English as a language is for use, not just for examination. Live broadcast, she gave children to do a demonstration, about their Spring Festival life, from which nature brought out the knowledge point.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo | by Xiao Mingjuan

The children in her own class, in addition to reciting all the new words and phrases that day, could draw inferences and write a short essay using the new grammar. By the afternoon, however, some of the children in the helped areas had not yet figured out the words and grammar.

This has something to do with the difference in the supply of students from both places. Xiao Mingjuan's Gulou experimental primary school, a key primary school in Gulou District, has a good supply of students, most of whom come from families with "double-high" economic conditions and quality parents. Some parents take their children to the cinema to see the minions, must see the original pronunciation, "from the details of education to cultivate children. ".

From the parents feedback photos, Xiao Mingjuan also saw that the children in her class almost all use the computer, large screen, not hurt the eyes, photo background mostly in the study, clean and bright. Some children can use their laptops to view lesson plans and then use tablets to play live lessons, while mobile phones are used to receive messages from wechat groups.

Students listen to a live broadcast class at Gulou experimental primary school

Huang Qian, a fifth grader at Dongguan Primary School in Min County, 2,000 km away, does not have the option of an online learning facility.

Money is tight at home, there is no computer to buy, mother is working outside again, Huang Qian and elder sister can share father's mobile phone only, watch live broadcast lesson together. The home does not have the Wifi, they use the flow, the live broadcast ends, immediately quit the network page, prevents the flow waste.

Never online classes, the live broadcast of the teacher, Huang Qian felt "strange, like through what" , took two days to adapt, Huang Qian accepted himself "more than a teacher. ". On study, Huang Qian did not think too urgent goal, feel oneself do good preparation and review good. But on the live broadcast after class, send and receive homework in the Wechat Group, Huang Qian and sister only a mobile phone, can only stagger the time to use.

Compared with Huang Qian, Liu Xiaoran, a sixth grader at Songxi Experimental Primary School in Nanping County, takes her time. Her parents attach importance to education and bought her a tablet dedicated to her study.

But parents remain cautious about other investments. Xiao ran realized that they do not know how to write essays, parents quickly found the network composition to improve the class, is the experience version. Xiao ran listened for five days, feeling fruitful, but the parents have not decided whether to buy her 1800 yuan worth of formal courses.

Xiao ran studied very hard and got 96 points in the English exam at the end of last term. She thought she didn't play well. Affected by the epidemic, delayed start of school, she is most worried about the problem is to delay learning, heard that can listen to live classes, Xiao ran excitedly sitting at the desk, but did not think of the screen of the teachers "speak a little fast, a little hard to understand. ".

Finding this, Xiao ran decided to preview in advance, but she did not borrow a Chinese textbook. Unlike city children who have a printer and photocopier all in one, Xiao ran could not print out the text and handouts, and could only preview them on the screen, will focus on a word-by-word copy in the book, and then according to the playback of the live class to learn again.

After adapting to the rhythm of the live broadcast class, Xiao ran also noticed the difference between it and the usual class. In English class, Xiao ran found that even "retell the text" teachers are expressed in English, the whole process did not speak Mandarin. This is Xiao ran's first all-english class.

Qingbei net school "classroom in the air" broke through the educational barriers in front of Xiao Ran, so that high-quality educational resources to the screen as a carrier, flow in all corners.

Not only can teachers teach online, control the broadcasting room in real time, check the number of students attending class and analyze the course data, but students can also have a convenient class at multiple terminals, such as mobile and PC, and preview the knowledge points in class ahead of time, the online comments interact with the teacher and can then be replayed many times over.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure | classroom in the sky web interface

Qingbei, which originally focused on online tutoring for primary and secondary school courses, has set up free "classroom in the sky" for thousands of primary and secondary schools in nearly 20 provinces, including Fujian, Guangzhou and Hubei, during the outbreak. With the strong technical support of the live broadcast room, the "classroom in the air" has realized the equal sharing of educational resources, and the children stand on the same starting line.

This time, the Gulou District teacher chosen for the live broadcast is teaching almost every class at an open standard. A few days after the start of the class, Feng Haiyan clearly felt the enthusiasm of the students. One day, she opened her cell phone more than 8:00 in the morning, and found that just before 6:00, there were students in the group punching in and starting to study.

Feng was going to wait for the children to finish their Chinese and math classes, and then set their English homework in the afternoon. Unexpectedly, at noon, a student asked on Wechat: "Teacher, what's the homework for today? " The student had already finished the previewing of the course.

The subversion of the form of the curriculum also reminded Pei Meiling of the hard times when there was no heat in the classroom and no coal stove. In order to save coal after school, it could not be regenerated. Instead, the sun was in the playground and it was a little warmer than the classroom. The children who loved to study, he took the chalk and wrote ancient poems on the ground in the playground.

Students listen to a live lecture at Dongzhao Primary School in Min County, Gansu Province

In the classroom in the air, Pei Meiling feels that teachers are more like magicians than teachers, "children can absorb the knowledge like a sponge at home. ".

For mei-ling Pei, who has taught in the mountains for 20 years, this is the scene of her dreams.

* Liu Yun, Huang Qian and Liu Xiaoran were pseudonyms.
